title: Policy2100(F)
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

* Advise and assist the Board in policy development and strategic planning.
* Provide professional recommendations and information to support informed decision-making.
* Attend and participate in all Board meetings (unless excused) and ensure that necessary data and reports are provided in a timely manner.

The Superintendent may delegate responsibilities necessary to carry out the daily operation of the school system to other district officials as appropriate and develop procedures to ensure efficient operation of the schools.
